<font color="#FF0000">THE METAL OF THE MAN</font><br>
<tt>Wed Feb 18 13:26:11 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Honor is an exhibit of the worth of the man not the medals he wears.  There are many heroes but only a few were given the opportunity to risk or give their lives in the performance of an act that they accomplished with out forethought or consideration of medals.  It is we who gave them a medal.  It is they who performed the act.<br><br>
I honor and respect the man not just the medals he wears.  It is a rare opportunity to know the man whose medals do not exhibit his true worth as a member of our cadre.<br><br>
I know the man Ed Ramon.  A friendship I value.  He just happens to be highly decorated.  I accept that as a fact.<br><br>
When you feel good about yourself the talk of medals dim in comparison.<br>

<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


